record_data.record_plain_text:
PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO (PNM) RESERVE ENERGY SERVICE TARIFF FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF, VOLUME NO. 9 1. Applicability: This tariff governs the sale of Reserve Energy Service by Public Service Company of New Mexico ("Seller").
2. Definitions: a. "Day-Ahead Price" means the Mid-C Day Ahead Price or the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Price. b. "ICE" means Intercontinental Exchange, Inc., or any successor organization. c. "Mid-C Day-Ahead Price" means (a) for On-Peak Hours, the Mid-Columbia Day-Ahead Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings "Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Mid C Peak" or any successor headings and (b) for Off-Peak Hours, the Mid-Columbia Day-Ahead Off-Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings "Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Mid C Off-Peak" or any successor headings. d. "NERC" means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation, or a successor organization that is responsible for establishing reliability criteria and protocols. e. "NWPP RSG Committee" means the committee established under the terms of the NWPP Agreement to administer the NWPP Reserve Sharing Program. f. "Off-Peak Hours" means all hours ending 01:00 PPT through 06:00 PPT and hours ending 23:00 PPT through 24:00 PPT, Monday through Saturday and hours ending 01:00 PPT through 24:00 PPT, on Sundays and NERC designated holidays. g. "On-Peak Hours" means all hours ending 07:00 PPT through 22:00 PPT, Monday through Saturday, excluding NERC designated holidays. h. "Palo Verde Day-Ahead Price" means (a) for On-Peak Hours, the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings "Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Palo Verde Peak" or any successor headings and (b) for Off-Peak Hours, the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Off-Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings "Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Palo Verde Off-Peak" or any successor headings. i. "Request Hour" means the hour during which the participant first requests Reserve Energy Service. j. "Reserve Energy Service" means reserve energy provided pursuant to the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, or any successor procedure thereto. k. "WECC Soft Price Cap" means the price cap adopted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission in San Diego Gas & Electric Company v. Sellers of Energy and Ancillary Services, 93 FERC 61,121 (2000) and Western Electric Coordinating Council, 133 FERC 61,026 (2010), subject to the guidance provided by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission in ConocoPhillips Company, et al., 175 FERC 61,226 (2021). 3. Availability: Reserve Energy Service shall be available to any entity ("Buyer") that has agreed to share reserves pursuant to the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, or any successor procedure thereto.
4. Rates: Consistent with the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, settlement of Reserve Energy Service during the hour(s) in which Reserve Energy Service is at the Settlement Price, which will be the average of the Mid-C Day-Ahead Price and the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Price for the Request Hour; provided, however, that if ICE does not publish a Day-Ahead Price for a relevant operating day or Request Hour, then the Settlement Price shall be the average of the other Day-Head Price for the Request Hour and in no event will the Settlement Price be less than zero or greater than the WECC Soft Price Cap in effect as of the Request Hour.
5. Billing and Settlements: Financial Settlement: Financial Settlements will occur under the Seller's normal monthly billing cycle, unless otherwise mutually agreed.
